        "content": "<p>Is there a function that creates a list by concatenating <code>n</code> copies of the same list?<br>\nThere is <code>list.repeat (a : α) : ℕ → list α</code> that repeats a single element.<br>\nIs there a similar function <code>list α → ℕ → list α</code> for repeating lists?</p>",
        "id": 273408341,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Dvořák",
        "timestamp": 1645974515
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/list.join\">docs#list.join</a> on <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/list.repeat\">docs#list.repeat</a></p>",
        "id": 273408681,
